  "text": "The DQI-R score was based on methods by Haines et al [CITATION_1] and adapted for our FFQ by Newby et al [CITATION_2] Briefly, the DQI-R consists of 10 components that measure intake of several food groups and nutrients and diet diversity and moderation. The range of possible scores for each component is 0 -10 points, depending on the level of intake, and the maximum possible DQI-R score is 100 points.",
